      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/11/65",
      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ أَشْتَرِي مِائَةَ رَاوِيَةٍ مِنْ زَيْتٍ وَ أَعْتَرِضُ رَاوِيَةً أَوِ اِثْنَتَيْنِ وَ أَتَّزِنُهُمَا ثُمَّ آخُذُ سَائِرَهُ عَلَى قَدْرِ ذَلِكَ فَقَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3836 - It is narrated from Abdul-Malik bin Amr who said:\nI said to Abu Abdillah (as), \"I purchase one hundred containers of oil, and I inspect one or two containers and weigh them, then take the rest based on that measurement.\"\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm.\""
        ]
      }
    },
